63. expostulationem] This word per- haps suggested to Hutten the title which he gave to his attack on Erasmus (HE. 310). It was written after seein Ep. 1342 in print, probably therefore in April or May; and was printed by John Schott at Strasburg during the summer, not long before Erasmus’ reply, the Sponqia (Ep. 1378), which followed it quickly. For the circumstances of the composition and publication of the

Expostulatio see the Sponqia (LB. x. 1633 E-1634A = HE· 333, §5 19—21); also Ep. 1383. 1-9, and LB. App. 346, 173501). Though Melanchthon con- demns Hutten’s action as early as 3 July, he did not see the book till August (ME 245, 247, 253-5 ; cf· 273, 291) ; but a copy had certainly reached Zurich by 13 July (VE. 353).
